    </section>

    <p>DUBAI • Ma­hen­dra Singh Dhoni has be­come the most-capped In­dian Premier League (IPL) player, even as his Chen­nai Su­per Kings team – cur­rently bot­tom of the ta­ble – fal­tered in yet an­other run chase.</p>
    <p>The 39-year-old has now played 194 IPL matches, and on Fri­day over­took his for­mer In­dia and CSK team­mate Suresh Raina, who has 193 games. Dhoni, the ex-In­dia skip­per, and Raina, an­nounced their re­tire­ment from in­ter­na­tional cricket last month.</p>


